cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and creating sentence embeddings. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new architecture for auto-encoding text paragraphs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with building NLP systems, including conversational agents. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for text encoding, which are commonly used in computer vision. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper proposes alternations to the recursive convolutional architecture to improve accuracy and reduce training time, which involves neural network optimization.
